co!\\\"\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1722, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Cries\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"Remco, Remco, Remco\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1720}]}, {\"sentence\": \"bellowed out as history was being made.\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1762, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1746}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just one final push up the 1km climb and 9.4km run back to the Eiffel Tower separated him from double gold at Paris 2024, and becoming the first man to claim both the Olympic time trial and race.\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Just one final push\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1783}, {\"ngram\": \"9.4km\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1810}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"double gold\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 1870}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1879}, {\"ngram\": \"the first man\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1912}, {\"ngram\": \"both the Olympic time trial\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 1949}, {\"ngram\": \"race\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 1958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And among the madness, it felt an almost overwhelming privilege to witness from the roadside as one of the best riders in the world, a talent of a generation, soloed past to roars that crescendoed as he approached.\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 2174, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the madness\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1981}, {\"ngram\": \"an almost overwhelming privilege\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2023}, {\"ngram\": \"the roadside\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2052}, {\"ngram\": \"the best riders\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2078}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2091}, {\"ngram\": \"a talent\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"a generation\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2117}, {\"ngram\": \"roars\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2139}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Evenepoel's triumph not only showed off to the world the joy of the bike racing itself but also highlighted professional cycling's best asset - being free to watch.\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel's triumph\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2194}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2218, \"to\": 2227}, {\"ngram\": \"the joy\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2235}, {\"ngram\": \"the bike\", \"from\": 2239, \"to\": 2247}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While famous sights of La Trocadero, the Grand Palais and even the foot of the Eiffel Tower have been turned into wonderful venues for the Paris games to host Skateboarding, fencing and beach volleyball to show off the City of Light's best offerings, none could beat that of the 18th arrondissement and it'sgratuitentry fee.\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2369, \"end\": 2378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.103481573822455e-12, \"text\": \"Trocadero\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\"}, {\"begin\": 2482, \"end\": 2487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.345264203563413e-56, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"famous sights\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2362}, {\"ngram\": \"the Grand Palais\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2396}, {\"ngram\": \"even the foot\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 2414}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 2418, \"to\": 2434}, {\"ngram\": \"wonderful venues\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2473}, {\"ngram\": \"host\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2501}, {\"ngram\": \"Skateboarding\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2515}, {\"ngram\": \"fencing\", \"from\": 2517, \"to\": 2524}, {\"ngram\": \"beach\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2534}, {\"ngram\": \"volleyball\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2545}, {\"ngram\": \"the City\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2566}, {\"ngram\": \"Light's best offerings\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2592}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2598}, {\"ngram\": \"the 18th arrondissement\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2641}, {\"ngram\": \"it'sgratuitentry fee\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2666}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So rather than being in the mixed zone or press room with fellow journalists, for the price of eight hours of my time, a few thousand steps uphill and a willingness to accept possible sunburn I secured a spot insport's best arena - Montmartre Hill.\", \"from\": 2668, \"to\": 2916, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the mixed zone\", \"from\": 2692, \"to\": 2706}, {\"ngram\": \"press room\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2720}, {\"ngram\": \"fellow journalists\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2744}, {\"ngram\": \"the price\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2759}, {\"ngram\": \"eight hours\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2774}, {\"ngram\": \"my time\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 2785}, {\"ngram\": \"possible sunburn\", \"from\": 2843, \"to\": 2859}, {\"ngram\": \"a spot insport's best arena - Montmartre Hill\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2915}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 2918, \"to\": 3020, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The latest race content\", \"from\": 2918, \"to\": 2941}, {\"ngram\": \"interviews\", \"from\": 2943, \"to\": 2953}, {\"ngram\": \"features\", \"from\": 2955, \"to\": 2963}, {\"ngram\": \"reviews\", \"from\": 2965, \"to\": 2972}, {\"ngram\": \"expert buying guides\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2997}, {\"ngram\": \"your inbox\", \"from\": 3009, \"to\": 3019}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 9:30am, I made my way over to the Rue Lepic, having identified it as the place to be for the race the night before on my own (walking) reconnoitre of the 272.1km course's hardest point where I would see the riders three times on the 18km Paris circuit.\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3263, \"end\": 3268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.345264203563413e-56, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my way\", \"from\": 3040, \"to\": 3046}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rue Lepic\", \"from\": 3055, \"to\": 3068}, {\"ngram\": \"the place\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3103}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3122}, {\"ngram\": \"my own (walking) reconnoitre\", \"from\": 3143, \"to\": 3171}, {\"ngram\": \"the 272.1km course's hardest point\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3209}, {\"ngram\": \"the riders\", \"from\": 3228, \"to\": 3238}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This may sound early to the untrained cycling spectator but I was far from the first there, with flags from all around the world already being tied to the barriers and any surrounding walls that could take it upon arrival.\", \"from\": 3279, \"to\": 3501, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the untrained cycling spectator\", \"from\": 3303, \"to\": 3334}, {\"ngram\": \"flags\", \"from\": 3376, \"to\": 3381}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3407}, {\"ngram\": \"the barriers\", \"from\": 3430, \"to\": 3442}, {\"ngram\": \"any surrounding walls\", \"from\": 3447, \"to\": 3468}, {\"ngram\": \"arrival\", \"from\": 3493, \"to\": 3500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French, Belgian, British, Basque and Danish were among them but the best effort was from the Dutch fan I plotted up next to, who took tape from a local notice to ensure his \\\"Fokking yes\\\" blue red and white flag was on show.\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3725, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3528, \"end\": 3534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basques\", \"score\": 0.9245547329326865, 