\"from\": 3889, \"to\": 3895}, {\"ngram\": \"the afternoon\", \"from\": 3903, \"to\": 3916}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 3924, \"to\": 3932}, {\"ngram\": \"city bikes\", \"from\": 3936, \"to\": 3946}, {\"ngram\": \"budding cyclists\", \"from\": 3948, \"to\": 3964}, {\"ngram\": \"the course\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 3985}, {\"ngram\": \"the run club\", \"from\": 3989, \"to\": 4001}, {\"ngram\": \"laps\", \"from\": 4013, \"to\": 4017}, {\"ngram\": \"the hill\", \"from\": 4021, \"to\": 4029}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 4039, \"to\": 4047}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One young fan in a Man City shirt would have felt a cheer equal to any he could've at the Etihad Stadium as he fought up the cobbles on a Boardman mountain bike, while even the gendarmes were in great spirits as they high-fived the bread, beer and wine-fuelled crowds.\", \"from\": 4050, \"to\": 4318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4069, \"end\": 4077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_City_F.C.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3562984276992853e-24, \"text\": \"Man City\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_City_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_City_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 4188, \"end\": 4196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boardman_High_School\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.127210223032069e-14, \"text\": \"Boardman\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3914\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boardman_High_School\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boardman_High_School\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One young fan\", \"from\": 4050, \"to\": 4063}, {\"ngram\": \"a cheer\", \"from\": 4100, \"to\": 4107}, {\"ngram\": \"the Etihad Stadium\", \"from\": 4136, \"to\": 4154}, {\"ngram\": \"the cobbles\", \"from\": 4171, \"to\": 4182}, {\"ngram\": \"even the gendarmes\", \"from\": 4218, \"to\": 4236}, {\"ngram\": \"great spirits\", \"from\": 4245, \"to\": 4258}, {\"ngram\": \"the bread\", \"from\": 4278, \"to\": 4287}, {\"ngram\": \"beer\", \"from\": 4289, \"to\": 4293}, {\"ngram\": \"wine-fuelled crowds\", \"from\": 4298, \"to\": 4317}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The roars for Evenepoel the champion had been ringing out almost at as many decibels for several hours before his crowning arrival.\", \"from\": 4319, \"to\": 4450, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The roars\", \"from\": 4319, \"to\": 4328}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 4333, \"to\": 4342}, {\"ngram\": \"the champion\", \"from\": 4343, \"to\": 4355}, {\"ngram\": \"as many decibels\", \"from\": 4387, \"to\": 4403}, {\"ngram\": \"several hours\", \"from\": 4408, \"to\": 4421}, {\"ngram\": \"his crowning arrival\", \"from\": 4429, \"to\": 4449}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the biggest cheers of the morning came when a huge green Montmartre Velo Club flag was hoisted out of a window above the road, with each local who emerged from their window and addressed the crowd being acclaimed like the Pope emerging from his balcony in the Vatican.\", \"from\": 4452, \"to\": 4727, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the biggest cheers\", \"from\": 4459, \"to\": 4477}, {\"ngram\": \"the morning\", \"from\": 4481, \"to\": 4492}, {\"ngram\": \"a huge green Montmartre Velo Club flag\", \"from\": 4503, \"to\": 4541}, {\"ngram\": \"a window\", \"from\": 4561, \"to\": 4569}, {\"ngram\": \"the road\", \"from\": 4576, \"to\": 4584}, {\"ngram\": \"their window\", \"from\": 4619, \"to\": 4631}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 4646, \"to\": 4655}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pope\", \"from\": 4677, \"to\": 4685}, {\"ngram\": \"his balcony\", \"from\": 4700, \"to\": 4711}, {\"ngram\": \"the Vatican\", \"from\": 4715, \"to\": 4726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the barriers filling well in advance of the first passage due around 4:30pm, the waiting game continued and anticipation built, with a new group arriving behind every few minutes to try and ensure they had a spot to see the riders.\", \"from\": 4729, \"to\": 4965, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the barriers\", \"from\": 4734, \"to\": 4746}, {\"ngram\": \"advance\", \"from\": 4763, \"to\": 4770}, {\"ngram\": \"the first passage\", \"from\": 4774, \"to\": 4791}, {\"ngram\": \"the waiting game\", \"from\": 4811, \"to\": 4827}, {\"ngram\": \"anticipation\", \"from\": 4842, \"to\": 4854}, {\"ngram\": \"a new group\", \"from\": 4867, \"to\": 4878}, {\"ngram\": \"every few minutes\", \"from\": 4895, \"to\": 4912}, {\"ngram\": \"a spot\", \"from\": 4940, \"to\": 4946}, {\"ngram\": \"the riders\", \"from\": 4954, \"to\": 4964}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was sport at its best and cycling spectating at its purest - riders hours away but the atmosphere all the same - electric.\", \"from\": 4966, \"to\": 5091, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 4973, \"to\": 4978}, {\"ngram\": \"its purest - riders\", \"from\": 5017, \"to\": 5036}, {\"ngram\": \"the atmosphere\", \"from\": 5052, \"to\": 5066}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having caught glimpses of the race on a buffering stream, I was aware Ben Healy had got away in a group after the two early breakaway moves faded before the Paris circuit, but I did not quite expect his aero helmet and recognisable low-profile style to be the first things I saw round the corner in front of the Moulin de la Galette restaurant.\", \"from\": 5095, \"to\": 5439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5165, \"end\": 5174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.34396645928694e-31, \"text\": \"Ben Healy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\"}, {\"begin\": 5252, \"end\": 5257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.345264203563413e-56, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5407, \"end\": 5427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_de_la_Galette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Moulin de la Galette\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_de_la_Galette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moulin_de_la_Galette\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"glimpses\", \"from\": 5109, \"to\": 5117}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 5121, \"to\": 5129}, {\"ngram\": \"a buffering stream\", \"from\": 5133, \"to\": 5151}, {\"ngram\": \"a group\", \"from\": 5191, \"to\": 5198}, {\"ngram\": \"the two early breakaway moves\", \"from\": 5205, \"to\": 5234}, {\"ngram\": \"his aero helmet\", \"from\": 5294, \"to\": 5309}, {\"ngram\": \"recognisable low-profile style\", \"from\": 5314, \"to\": 5344}, {\"ngram\": \"the first things\", \"from\": 5351, \"to\": 5367}, {\"ngram\": \"the corner\", \"from\": 5380, \"to\": 5390}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 5394, \"to\": 5399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That site and its famous windmill were once the setting for Pierre-Auguste Renoir's 1876 work, Bal du moulin de la Galette, however, while the joy and dance of the scene representing Parisian life that the Frenchman tried to capture took on different forms, they were present all the same at the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 5441, \"to\": 5751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5501, \"end\": 5522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre-Auguste_Renoir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre-Auguste Renoir\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre-Auguste_Renoir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre-Auguste_Renoir\"}, {\"begin\": 5624, \"end\": 5637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parisian_Life_(1936_film)\", \"score\": 0.7158307388773035, \"rank\": 0.3969780219779311, \"text\": \"Parisian life\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parisian_Life_(1936_film)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parisian_Life_(1936_film)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That site\", \"from\": 5441, \"to\": 5450}, {\"ngram\": \"its famous windmill\", \"from\": 5455, \"to\": 5474}, {\"ngram\": \"the setting\", \"from\": 5485, \"to\": 5496}, {\"ngram\": \"du moulin de la Galette\", \"from\": 5540, \"to\": 5563}, {\"ngram\": \"the joy\", \"from\": 5580, \"to\": 5587}, {\"ngram\": \"dance\", \"from\": 5592, \"to\": 5597}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene\", \"from\": 5601, \"to\": 5610}, {\"ngram\": \"the Frenchman\", \"from\": 5643, \"to\": 5656}, {\"ngram\": \"different forms\", \"from\": 5682, \"to\": 5697}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 5733, \"to\": 5750}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The jubilation of the fans contrasted with the pain on the riders' faces, while the dance was taken on by a certainMathieu van der Poel, who smashed his way up the cobbles as if it were the Oude Kwaremont or Paterberg at the Tour of Flanders.\", \"from\": 5753, \"to\": 5995, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5961, \"end\": 5970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paterberg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paterberg\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paterberg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paterberg\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The jubilation\", \"from\": 5753, \"to\": 5767}, {\"ngram\": \"the fans\", \"from\": 5771, \"to\": 5779}, {\"ngram\": \"the pain\", \"from\": 5796, \"to\": 5804}, {\"ngram\": \"the riders' faces\", \"from\": 5808, \"to\": 5825}, {\"ngram\": \"the dance\", \"from\": 5833, \"to\": 5842}, {\"ngram\": \"a certainMathieu van der Poel\", \"from\": 5859, \"to\": 5888}, {\"ngram\": \"his way\", \"from\": 5902, \"to\": 5909}, {\"ngram\": \"the cobbles\", \"from\": 5913, \"to\": 5924}, {\"ngram\": \"the Oude Kwaremont\", \"from\": 5939, \"to\": 5957}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tour\", \"from\": 5974, \"to\": 5982}, {\"ngram\": \"Flanders\", \"from\": 5986, \"to\": 5994}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His explosive pace, which only close rival Wout van Aert could match, turned the Rue Lepic into a scene more akin to Monet's La Rue Montorgueil, \\u00e0 Paris, 1878.\", \"from\": 5997, \"to\": 6156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6040, \"end\": 6053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wout van Aert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\"}, {\"begin\": 6114, \"end\": 6119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Monet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.550360182316504e-79, \"text\": \"Monet\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Monet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Claude_Monet\"}, {\"begin\": 6144, \"end\": 6149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.345264203563413e-56, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His explosive pace\", \"from\": 5997, \"to\": 6015}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rue Lepic\", \"from\": 6074, \"to\": 6087}, {\"ngram\": \"a scene\", \"from\": 6093, \"to\": 6100}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is, if you replace the French flags hanging out the windows with the fans who had climbed gutters, apartment fences and lamp posts to reach a vantage point and cheer on cycling's best.\", \"from\": 6157, \"to\": 6346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6185, \"end\": 6191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9246766070717087, \"rank\": 0.08140879257123257, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the windows\", \"from\": 6210, \"to\": 6221}, {\"ngram\": \"the fans\", \"from\": 6227, \"to\": 6235}, {\"ngram\": \"gutters\", \"from\": 6252, \"to\": 6259}, {\"ngram\": \"apartment fences\", \"from\": 6261, \"to\": 6277}, {\"ngram\": \"lamp posts\", \"from\": 6282, \"to\": 6292}, {\"ngram\": \"a vantage point\", \"from\": 6302, \"to\": 6317}, {\"ngram\": \"cycling\", \"from\": 6331, \"to\": 6338}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's hard to describe how fast Van Der Poel and Van Aert were going but it's a pace that truly stuns an onlooker having seen hundreds go up it before the race's arrival at a third of the pace.\", \"from\": 6348, \"to\": 6540, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"how fast Van Der Poel\", \"from\": 6370, \"to\": 6391}, {\"ngram\": \"Van Aert\", \"from\": 6396, \"to\": 6404}, {\"ngram\": \"a pace\", \"from\": 6425, \"to\": 6431}, {\"ngram\": \"an onlooker\", \"from\": 6449, \"to\": 6460}, {\"ngram\": \"hundreds\", \"from\": 6473, \"to\": 6481}, {\"ngram\": \"the race's arrival\", \"from\": 6498, \"to\": 6516}, {\"ngram\": \"a third\", \"from\": 6520, \"to\": 6527}, {\"ngram\": \"the pace\", \"from\": 6531, \"to\": 6539}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A pace so high, that I did not even see or really think about where Remco Evenepoel was on the first ascent of Montmartre - he wasn't in the front so why would I have considered him?\", \"from\": 6541, \"to\": 6723, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A pace\", \"from\": 6541, \"to\": 6547}, {\"ngram\": \"Remco Evenepoel\", \"from\": 6609, \"to\": 6624}, {\"ngram\": \"the first ascent\", \"from\": 6632, \"to\": 6648}, {\"ngram\": \"Montmartre\", \"from\": 6652, \"to\": 6662}, {\"ngram\": \"the front\", \"from\": 6678, \"to\": 6687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can imagine my surprise upon learning he was attacking from the group of favourites seven kilometres later in what would be the decisive move of the day.\", \"from\": 6724, \"to\": 6881, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my surprise\", \"from\": 6740, \"to\": 6751}, {\"ngram\": \"the group\", \"from\": 6788, \"to\": 6797}, {\"ngram\": \"favourites\", \"from\": 6801, \"to\": 6811}, {\"ngram\": \"the decisive move\", \"from\": 6852, \"to\": 6869}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 6873, \"to\": 6880}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still thinking about how good yesterday's #CyclingRoad race was.\", \"from\": 6883, \"to\": 6947, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"yesterday's #CyclingRoad race\", \"from\": 6913, \"to\": 6942}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Best bits I saw\\ud83d\\udcf8- MVDP and WVA smashing up Montmartre- Rwanda's Eric Manizabayo bringing the vibes and Olympic spirit after being in the break- Madouas giving everything to hang onto silver pic.twitter.com/oypq90spoLAugust 4, 2024 By this point up the hill in Montmartre, the bustling crowd had broken out into song, be it French national anthem La Marseillaise for the second or third time, Joe Dassin's Les Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es or simply \\\"Cha la la la la la la, Thibaut Pinot!\\\"\", \"from\": 6948, \"to\": 7422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6976, \"end\": 6979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WVA\", \"score\": 0.9124264196728243, \"rank\": 0.09597878605267451, \"text\": \"WVA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WVA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WVA\"}, {\"begin\": 7004, \"end\": 7010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rwanda\", \"score\": 0.9999661306389113, \"rank\": 3.3870505851103036e-05, \"text\": \"Rwanda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rwanda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rwanda\"}, {\"begin\": 7093, \"end\": 7100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 7210, \"end\": 7220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.892351370393475e-53, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}, {\"begin\": 7273, \"end\": 7295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French national anthem\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\"}, {\"begin\": 7296, \"end\": 7311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.501693375071073e-76, \"text\": \"La Marseillaise\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Marseillaise\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Best bits\", \"from\": 6948, \"to\": 6957}, {\"ngram\": \"\\ud83d\\udcf8- MVDP\", \"from\": 6963, \"to\": 6970}, {\"ngram\": \"the vibes\", \"from\": 7037, \"to\": 7046}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic spirit\", \"from\": 7051, \"to\": 7065}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 7107, \"to\": 7117}, {\"ngram\": \"silver pic.twitter.com/oypq90spoLAugust\", \"from\": 7131, \"to\": 7170}, {\"ngram\": \"this point\", \"from\": 7182, \"to\": 7192}, {\"ngram\": \"the hill\", \"from\": 7196, \"to\": 7204}, {\"ngram\": \"the bustling crowd\", \"from\": 7220, \"to\": 7238}, {\"ngram\": \"song\", \"from\": 7259, \"to\": 7263}, {\"ngram\": \"the second or third time\", \"from\": 7314, \"to\": 7338}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"from\": 7364, \"to\": 7371}, {\"ngram\": \"la la\", \"from\": 7399, \"to\": 7404}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- TheVirage Pinotmade it all the way from the Col du Petit Ballon to the Olympic road race.\", \"from\": 7423, \"to\": 7514, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7470, \"end\": 7489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Col_du_Petit_Ballon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Col du Petit Ballon\", \"types\": [\"Q133056\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Col_du_Petit_Ballon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Col_du_Petit_Ballon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"- TheVirage Pinotmade\", \"from\": 7423, \"to\": 7444}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic road race\", \"from\": 7492, \"to\": 7513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The atmosphere was electric, infectious and one only bettered by the display being put on by Evenepoel, Madouas, Healy, Van der Poel, Van Aert and all of the willing bunch who put on a show in pursuit of Olympic glory.\", \"from\": 7515, \"to\": 7733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7620, \"end\": 7627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The atmosphere\", \"from\": 7515, \"to\": 7529}, {\"ngram\": \"the display\", \"from\": 7580, \"to\": 7591}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 7608, \"to\": 7617}, {\"ngram\": \"Healy\", \"from\": 7628, \"to\": 7633}, {\"ngram\": \"Van der Poel\", \"from\": 7635, \"to\": 7647}, {\"ngram\": \"Van Aert\", \"from\": 7649, \"to\": 7657}, {\"ngram\": \"the willing bunch\", \"from\": 7669, \"to\": 7686}, {\"ngram\": \"a show\", \"from\": 7698, \"to\": 7704}, {\"ngram\": \"pursuit\", \"from\": 7708, \"to\": 7715}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic glory\", \"from\": 7719, \"to\": 7732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But for the latter pair, the medals slipped away as the tactics and dynamics of having smaller teams and no race radios saw their efforts fading and gaps getting insurmountable throughout the city circuit,even with Van der Poel's second burst on Rue Lepic.\", \"from\": 7735, \"to\": 7991, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7982, \"end\": 7991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rue_Lepic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rue Lepic\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rue_Lepic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rue_Lepic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the latter pair\", \"from\": 7743, \"to\": 7758}, {\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 7760, \"to\": 7770}, {\"ngram\": \"the tactics\", \"from\": 7787, \"to\": 7798}, {\"ngram\": \"dynamics\", \"from\": 7803, \"to\": 7811}, {\"ngram\": \"smaller teams\", \"from\": 7822, \"to\": 7835}, {\"ngram\": \"no race radios\", \"from\": 7840, \"to\": 7854}, {\"ngram\": \"their efforts\", \"from\": 7859, \"to\": 7872}, {\"ngram\": \"gaps\", \"from\": 7884, \"to\": 7888}, {\"ngram\": \"the city circuit\", \"from\": 7923, \"to\": 7939}, {\"ngram\": \"Van der Poel's second burst\", \"from\": 7950, \"to\": 7977}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I may have talked of groans when Madouas' gold rush ended, however, the French around me quickly turned their hopes to silver, accepting the dominance of a modern-day superstar in Evenepoel.\", \"from\": 7993, \"to\": 8183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8027, \"end\": 8034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 8066, \"end\": 8072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9246766070717087, \"rank\": 0.08140879257123257, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"groans\", \"from\": 8014, \"to\": 8020}, {\"ngram\": \"their hopes\", \"from\": 8097, \"to\": 8108}, {\"ngram\": \"the dominance\", \"from\": 8130, \"to\": 8143}, {\"ngram\": \"a modern-day superstar\", \"from\": 8147, \"to\": 8169}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 8173, \"to\": 8182}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The gap felt like an age when Madouas finally came by but he fought for all his worth on the final Montmartre ascent, mouth open and cadence faltering.\", \"from\": 8184, \"to\": 8335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8215, \"end\": 8222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 8284, \"end\": 8294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.892351370393475e-53, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The gap\", \"from\": 8184, \"to\": 8191}, {\"ngram\": \"an age\", \"from\": 8202, \"to\": 8208}, {\"ngram\": \"all his worth\", \"from\": 8256, \"to\": 8269}, {\"ngram\": \"mouth open and cadence faltering\", \"from\": 8302, \"to\": 8334}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was no chance of catching Evenepoel despite a few gasps, and screams of panic from the Belgian himself, when he required a late bike change for a puncture, but Madouas was holding off the charge behind him - some of whom, France's Christophe Laporte, had no clue whether they were fighting for a medal or not.\", \"from\": 8337, \"to\": 8652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8431, \"end\": 8438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9987823504588562, \"rank\": 0.0012191340189397501, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 8504, \"end\": 8511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 8566, \"end\": 8572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.378857904382664e-12, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 8575, \"end\": 8593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christophe Laporte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no chance\", \"from\": 8347, \"to\": 8356}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 8369, \"to\": 8378}, {\"ngram\": \"a few gasps\", \"from\": 8387, \"to\": 8398}, {\"ngram\": \"screams\", \"from\": 8404, \"to\": 8411}, {\"ngram\": \"panic\", \"from\": 8415, \"to\": 8420}, {\"ngram\": \"a late bike change\", \"from\": 8464, \"to\": 8482}, {\"ngram\": \"a puncture\", \"from\": 8487, \"to\": 8497}, {\"ngram\": \"the charge\", \"from\": 8527, \"to\": 8537}, {\"ngram\": \"no clue\", \"from\": 8598, \"to\": 8605}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 8637, \"to\": 8644}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the Pont d'I\\u00e9na and Eiffel Tower arrived, the Belgians around me cheered and broke into chants of Evenepoel's name again, only to be drowned out one minute and 16 seconds later, when both silver and bronze were captured by a Madouas and Laporte for a French team who were far from favourites to medal in the road race.\", \"from\": 8654, \"to\": 8975, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8678, \"end\": 8690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eiffel_Tower\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7175484743830554e-86, \"text\