f Leon Marchand in the pool and Teddy Riner on the tatami.\", \"from\": 9023, \"to\": 9210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9160, \"end\": 9168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Gabriel_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.6106278744183348, \"rank\": 0.6376586144151286, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Gabriel_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean_Gabriel_Marchand\"}, {\"begin\": 9185, \"end\": 9196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a national anthem\", \"from\": 9028, \"to\": 9045}, {\"ngram\": \"an awful lot\", \"from\": 9059, \"to\": 9071}, {\"ngram\": \"the past two weeks\", \"from\": 9078, \"to\": 9096}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 9103, \"to\": 9112}, {\"ngram\": \"the excellence\", \"from\": 9136, \"to\": 9150}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 9171, \"to\": 9179}, {\"ngram\": \"the tatami\", \"from\": 9199, \"to\": 9209}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming and Judo have been great highlights for Paris and France during this Olympics but the cycling men's road race and the half a million who turned out to witness it in person will be a sporting and Olympic moment indelibly etched into the history books.\", \"from\": 9211, \"to\": 9470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9225, \"end\": 9229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1499549546280897e-30, \"text\": \"Judo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judo\"}, {\"begin\": 9261, \"end\": 9266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.345264203563413e-56, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 9271, \"end\": 9277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.378857904382664e-12, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Swimming\", \"from\": 9211, \"to\": 9219}, {\"ngram\": \"great highlights\", \"from\": 9239, \"to\": 9255}, {\"ngram\": \"this Olympics\", \"from\": 9284, \"to\": 9297}, {\"ngram\": \"the cycling men's road race\", \"from\": 9302, \"to\": 9329}, {\"ngram\": \"person\", \"from\": 9385, \"to\": 9391}, {\"ngram\": \"a sporting and Olympic moment\", \"from\": 9400, \"to\": 9429}, {\"ngram\": \"the history books\", \"from\": 9452, \"to\": 9469}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now I opted against a second day on Montmartre Hill and watched the women's race on Pont d'I\\u00e9na, deciding to take in the glory of an historic start/finish line for cycling in front of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 9474, \"to\": 9675, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a second day\", \"from\": 9494, \"to\": 9506}, {\"ngram\": \"Montmartre Hill\", \"from\": 9510, \"to\": 9525}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's race\", \"from\": 9538, \"to\": 9554}, {\"ngram\": \"Pont d'I\\u00e9na\", \"from\": 9558, \"to\": 9569}, {\"ngram\": \"the glory\", \"from\": 9591, \"to\": 9600}, {\"ngram\": \"an historic start/finish line\", \"from\": 9604, \"to\": 9633}, {\"ngram\": \"cycling\", \"from\": 9638, \"to\": 9645}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 9649, \"to\": 9654}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 9658, \"to\": 9674}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smiles and ice vests were common for much of the 93-rider field, who would have recognised the sights on the Trocadero had they started the inaugural Tour de France Femmes in 2022.\", \"from\": 9677, \"to\": 9857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9787, \"end\": 9796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.103481573822455e-12, \"text\": \"Trocadero\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\"}, {\"begin\": 9828, \"end\": 9842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6593865697160154e-36, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Smiles\", \"from\": 9677, \"to\": 9683}, {\"ngram\": \"ice\", \"from\": 9688, \"to\": 9691}, {\"ngram\": \"vests\", \"from\": 9692, \"to\": 9697}, {\"ngram\": \"the 93-rider field\", \"from\": 9722, \"to\": 9740}, {\"ngram\": \"the sights\", \"from\": 9768, \"to\": 9778}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But soon focus descended on the start, with revered French rider and 1996 Olympic Road Race champion Jeannie Longo getting things going after a fitting round of applause from the riders.\", \"from\": 9859, \"to\": 10045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9912, \"end\": 9918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9246766070717087, \"rank\": 0.08140879257123257, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 9961, \"end\": 9974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeannie_Longo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeannie Longo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeannie_Longo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeannie_Longo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 9887, \"to\": 9896}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 9982, \"to\": 9988}, {\"ngram\": \"a fitting round\", \"from\": 10001, \"to\": 10016}, {\"ngram\": \"applause\", \"from\": 10020, \"to\": 10028}, {\"ngram\": \"the riders\", \"from\": 10034, \"to\": 10044}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It would be some time until I saw the field again, with a breathless 157.6km battle unfolding throughout the journey back to the famous bride.\", \"from\": 10047, \"to\": 10189, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some time\", \"from\": 10059, \"to\": 10068}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 10081, \"to\": 10090}, {\"ngram\": \"a breathless 157.6km battle\", \"from\": 10103, \"to\": 10130}, {\"ngram\": \"the journey\", \"from\": 10152, \"to\": 10163}, {\"ngram\": \"the famous bride\", \"from\": 10172, \"to\": 10188}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A crash ahead of the Montmartre Hill would have a huge effect on the race but the big screens in the finish area allowed for a much easier following of the action.\", \"from\": 10190, \"to\": 10353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10212, \"end\": 10222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.892351370393475e-53, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A crash\", \"from\": 10190, \"to\": 10197}, {\"ngram\": \"a huge effect\", \"from\": 10238, \"to\": 10251}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 10255, \"to\": 10263}, {\"ngram\": \"the big screens\", \"from\": 10268, \"to\": 10283}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish area\", \"from\": 10287, \"to\": 10302}, {\"ngram\": \"a much easier following\", \"from\": 10315, \"to\": 10338}, {\"ngram\": \"the action\", \"from\": 10342, \"to\": 10352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was no surprise in seeingKristen Faulkner (USA) round the final corner with 350 metres to go to take gold- that conclusion had become apparent much earlier when I realised she was going to win after Blanka Vas, Marianna Vos and Lotte Kopecky let her wheel go 3km from the line.\", \"from\": 10355, \"to\": 106